A '''cyclostyle''' (from the [[Greek language|Greek]] words for "circle" and "column") is a term used in [[architecture]]. A structure composed of a circular range of columns without a core is cyclostylar; with a core the range would be [[peristyle]]. This is the species of edifice called by [[Vitruvius]] monopteral.

